<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIGHT BROUGHT HAPPINESS TO EVERYBODY BUT FANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So, the over-hyped Tyson-Williams "fight" is officially over -- and everybody's 
happy! Right? Wrong! 
</P>
<P>
Promoter Don King is happy: another rich purse. 
</P>
<P>
Atlantic city host Donald Trump is happy: He was introduced to the crowd before 
the charade. 
</P>
<P>
The referee now has 39 fights in his resume. We still don't know how many were 
championship caliber; this one sure wasn't. 
</P>
<P>
Challenger Williams spent 93 seconds in the square circle and left a 
millionaire. 
</P>
<P>
Champion Tyson leaves the ring as a multimillionaire, plus a $100,000 cash 
bonus from Don King for the controversial knockdown. 
</P>
<P>
Everyone's happy! Right? Wrong! The crowd had every right to jeer and boo -- it 
was a ripoff. 
</P>
<P>
Add the jeers and boos from the HBO audience, and the decibel count goes off 
the meter. 
</P>
<P>
DAVID C. PHILLIPS 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
