<TEXT>
<P>
Concerning Claudia Puig's article on Rick Carroll, the radio programmer who 
died this month ("Carroll Brought Luster, Listeners to KROQ-FM," July 14): I 
was a deejay for 17 years, many of those working with or for Rick Carroll. Rick 
was able to instill a feeling of true security and protection, while making you 
feel like the world revolved around you. The feeling he gave you transferred to 
the performance you gave on the air and consequently to positive results in the 
ratings. 
</P>
