</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Doug Williams of the Washington Redskins was admitted to a Virginia 
hospital for treatment of a back injury. Williams said Sunday that he had 
suffered the injury about six weeks ago while running on a treadmill. 
</P>
<P>
Team officials said that Williams, who has already missed a week of training 
camp, will be in traction for at least a week. 
