<HEADLINE>
<P>
DATE, SITE SET FOR LEONARD-DURAN III 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sugar Ray Leonard and Roberto Duran will fight outdoors Dec. 7 at the Mirage 
Hotel in Las Vegas for Leonard's World Boxing Council super-middleweight title, 
Top Rank promoter Bob Arum announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The third Leonard-Duran bout was announced earlier in the week, but the date 
and location were undetermined. 
</P>
<P>
"The Mirage people more than satisfied my technical people," Arum said. "The 
fight will take place in a tent-like structure specially insulated from the 
wind." 
</P>
<P>
Leonard, 33, ended his retirement last Nov. 7 by stopping Donny Lalonde for the 
WBC middleweight and super-middleweight titles. Leonard relinquished the 
middleweight title now held by Duran, 38. 
</P>
