<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHINA HONORS MORE SOLDIERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese newspapers said Friday that 12 more soldiers have been named "Defenders 
of the Republic" for their role in crushing pro-democracy demonstrations in 
June, bringing to 22 the number awarded the title. 
</P>
<P>
An order signed by top leader Deng Xiaoping praised the 12 for bravery in 
breaching protesters' barricades, saving stricken comrades and other acts 
during the army assault on Tian An Men Square, the People's Daily said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
