<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Timothy Kelly, managing editor at the Orange County Register since 1987, is 
leaving the newspaper to become executive editor of the Lexington Herald-Leader 
in Lexington, Ky. No date for his departure has been set, although he is 
scheduled to leave within the next month. Before joining the Register, Kelly, 
41, was editor of the Daily News, based in Woodland Hills. 
</P>
