BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fremont to Buy S&amp;L in Fresno: Fremont General Corp. will acquire Tomar 
Financial Corp., a Fresno-based savings and loan, under an agreement signed by 
the two firms. The Santa Monica-based Fremont, which has insurance and 
financial service operations, will obtain Tomar's 14 branch offices in 
California. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<CORRECTION-DATE>
<P>
August 1, 1989, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</CORRECTION-DATE>
<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
Tomar Financial -- Tomar Financial of Fresno and its two Orange-based thrift 
and loan subsidiaries, Investors Thrift and Liberty Thrift &amp; Loan, are 
being acquired by Fremont General Corp. Tomar was incorrectly described as a 
savings and loan in Saturday's Briefly column. 
</P>
