<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Express Apologizes to Safra: American Express Co. said it apologized 
to international banker Edmond Safra for what it called "an unauthorized and 
shameful effort" to encourage false media reports that Safra's banks had been 
involved in money laundering. American Express also agreed to pay $4 million to 
charity as part of its unusual apology. In letters released by the two sides, 
American Express Chairman James D. Robinson III said people "acting on behalf 
of American Express began an unauthorized and shameful effort to use the media 
to malign" Safra and Republic National Bank of New York, in which Safra holds a 
33% stake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
