<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO VOTES ON PORTER RANCH PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Recent events regarding the development of the North Valley should disturb all 
of us! 
</P>
<P>
A huge Century City-type commercial development is seeking approval from the 
city. It would generate more than 160,000 car trips a day. Most days the air is 
nauseating. This will make our air deadly! The size of this development is 
unacceptable. Every other council member is fighting to zone down commercial 
property. The councilman is fighting to increase the zoning thirty times over. 
An effort to recall him is under way. 
</P>
<P>
The proposal is bad with regard to traffic, the air, the schools and the 
quality of life here. 
</P>
<P>
ROGER STRULL 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
