<P>
EL TORO JETS TO PRACTICE CARRIER LANDINGS AT BASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fighter attack aircraft will be practicing simulated aircraft carrier landings 
near the Marine Corps Air Station in El Toro in the evening hours next week, 
which may result in increased noise in surrounding neighborhoods, a spokeswoman 
at the station said. 
</P>
<P>
"Basically, it's something that happens all the time," said a Marine Corps 
spokeswoman. She said the FA-18 Hornet jets based at El Toro hold the practice 
sessions several times a year. They will be landing as if the runway at the air 
base were the deck of an aircraft carrier. 
</P>
<P>
The exercises are scheduled from 8:30 to 10:30 p.m. on Monday, Tuesday and 
Wednesday, according to the spokeswoman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
