<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAGUNA HILLS' SHEFF NAMED TO U.S. TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OKLAHOMA CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Outfielder Chris Sheff of Laguna Hills was one of five California players named 
to the 23-member U.S. team that will compete next month in the World Junior 
Baseball Championship in Canada. 
</P>
<P>
The world championship is scheduled Aug. 9-22 in Three Rivers, Quebec. The 
United States is the defending champion, having won its first title in the 
six-year-old competition last year in Australia. 
</P>
<P>
All of the players selected by the U.S. Baseball Federation competed in the 
U.S. Olympic Festival. 
</P>
<P>
Other California players named were infielder Jason Evans of Chatsworth, 
pitcher-infielder Danny Melendez of Los Angeles, pitcher Robert Wallace of 
Oxnard and catcher Greg Zaun of Glendale. 
