<HEADLINE>
<P>
HITS 3.4% IN JUNE; 
</P>
<P>
COUNTY'S JOBLESS RATE RISES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The unemployment rate in Orange County jumped to 3.4% in June, its highest 
reading since last July, but it was still the state's third lowest, behind 
Marin and San Mateo counties. The jobless rate was 3.1% in May. 
</P>
<P>
The state Employment Development Department reported 46,500 people out of work 
in the month, up from 42,000 in May. There were 1.17 million jobs in the county 
for June, up from 1.16 million last month. 
</P>
<P>
The increase in unemployment was probably due to the seasonal influx of 
students into the work force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
